<head>139	H.R. 1331 (Forty-third Congress, First Session &#8212; Grant)</head>
<p>For the relief of Joab Spencer and James R. Mead, for supplies furnished the Kansas tribe of Indians.</p>

<p>Vetoed May 12, 1874.  The veto message was laid before the House, referred to the Committee on Indian Affairs, and printed as H.R. Ex. Doc. No. 249 (2 <title>Cong. Rec.</title> 3826; <hi rend="italics">see also</hi> S. Misc. Doc. No. 53, 49th Cong., 2nd sess., p. 389).</p>

<p>Veto unchallenged.</p>



